  "text": "= 0.762(5) at L = 2 −6 L max (3.14) and the coupling value (u 6 ) entering the second factor in eq. (3.13) to lie safely in the perturbative regime -in order to obtain our central result Φ RGI Φ(µ) = 0.880 [CITATION_1] or Φ(µ) Φ RGI = 1.137(9) at µ = 1/L max (3.15) in the SF scheme 4 . Hence, through this analysis we have succeeded in connecting the lowand high-energy scales L = L max and L = 2 −6 L max non-perturbatively as intended. Note that, since the continuum limit has Φ RGI /Φ(L −1 max ) been taken, any regularization dependence has been removed from the result (3.15) so that ideally the error on Φ(µ)/Φ RGI of about 0.8% should only be included in estimates on matrix elements in the continuum limit.",
